Lumpy skin disease, Jordan
--------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 11 Jun 2013 from Dr Monther Al-Rifai, chief veterinary officer, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Amman, Jordan

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 20 Apr 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 25 Apr 2013
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Lumpy skin disease virus [LSDV]
Nature of diagnosis: suspicion, clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1: Al Adasyeh, Al Adasyeh, North Shuneh, Irbid
Date of start of the outbreak: 20 Apr 2013
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 1634 / 45 / 12 / 0 / 0
Affected population: about 8 dairy herds are located in Al Adasyeh. Clinical signs were seen on the cows: pyrexia, decrease in milk yield, enlarged lymph nodes; and 2-5 cm [0.8-2 in] nodules were developed all over the entire body.

Outbreak 2: El Muwaqqer, El Muwaqqer, El Muwaqqer, Amman
Date of start of the outbreak: 27 May 2013
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 2200 / 20 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: the infected dairy farm is located in El Muwaqqer. The cattle were vaccinated against sheep pox (10x). 7 days after vaccination, the 1st clinical signs of lumpy skin disease appeared in milking cows.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 3834 / 65 / 12 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics (rates are apparent and expressed as percentages)
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 1.70 / 0.31 / 18.46 / 0.31
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and /or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine, movement control inside the country, disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s), no vaccination, treatment of affected animals (antipyretics and antibiotics for secondary infections)
Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)

Diagnostic test results
1. Laboratory name and type: Central Animal Wealth Laboratory (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / real-time polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 25 Apr 2013 / Positive
2. Laboratory name and type: Institute for Animal Health, Pirbright (United Kingdom) (OIE's reference laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / PCR / 7 Jun 2013 / Positive

